Package org.lgdcloudsim.datacenter

Class ConflictHandlerResult

java.lang.Object
org.lgdcloudsim.datacenter.ConflictHandlerResult
public class ConflictHandlerResult extends Object
The result of the conflict handler. It contains the success result that the instances are allocated to the host successfully, and the failed result that the instances need to be rescheduled or be marked as failed.
Since:
LGDCloudSim 1.0
Author:
Jiawen Liu

    • addFailRes

      public void addFailRes(IntraScheduler intraScheduler, List<Instance> instances, Set<UserRequest> userRequests)
      Add the conflicted result that need to be rescheduled or be marked as failed, and the user requests that have exceeded the scheduling time limit. The user requests that have exceeded the scheduling time limit will be marked as failed directly. It is used to deal with the intra-scheduling results.
      Parameters:
      intraScheduler - the intra-scheduler
      instances - the conflicted instances that need to be rescheduled or be marked as failed
      userRequests - the user requests that have exceeded the scheduling time limit
